1142
00:42:14,166 --> 00:42:15,346
represents a molecule.

1143
00:42:15,346 --> 00:42:20,686
So capital N is just the number of up spins.

1144
00:42:20,686 --> 00:42:21,406
How do you

1145
00:42:21,406 --> 00:42:22,886
change the number of up spins?

1146
00:42:22,886 --> 00:42:26,566
How do you tune the system from,

1147
00:42:26,566 --> 00:42:27,526
essentially,

1148
00:42:27,526 --> 00:42:27,786
no

1149
00:42:27,786 --> 00:42:28,326
up spins,

1150
00:42:28,326 --> 00:42:31,586
and bias it towards lots of up spins?

1151
00:42:31,586 --> 00:42:33,346
You change H,

1152
00:42:33,346 --> 00:42:34,866
right?

1153
00:42:34,866 --> 00:42:36,566
When H is down,

1154
00:42:36,726 --> 00:42:38,326
it pushes all the spins down,

1155
00:42:38,326 --> 00:42:38,326
and when H goes up,

1156
00:42:38,326 --> 00:42:38,326
it pushes all the so-called up spins,

1157
00:42:38,326 --> 00:42:39,646
Now no matter what the temperature is,

1158
00:42:39,646 --> 00:42:40,886
if H is down,

1159
00:42:40,886 --> 00:42:45,046
it will bias the system toward few upspins.

1160
00:42:45,366 --> 00:42:49,046
And if you want to change the density of upspins,

1161
00:42:49,046 --> 00:42:51,946
what you do is move along this H-axis.

1162
00:42:52,226 --> 00:42:55,966
So the H-axis is closely connected.

1163
00:42:55,966 --> 00:42:58,486
It's essentially the same as the chemical potential.

1164
00:42:59,686 --> 00:43:02,396
And it's the thing that you tune

1165
00:43:02,396 --> 00:43:05,106
to change the density of the gas,

1166
00:43:05,106 --> 00:43:07,346
the density of the fluid.

1167
00:43:07,346 --> 00:43:08,786
Quick question.

1168
00:43:08,786 --> 00:43:12,316
The terminology is one Lagrange multiplier is beta

1169
00:43:12,316 --> 00:43:15,846
and the other Lagrange multiplier is beta mu?

1170
00:43:16,246 --> 00:43:16,446
Well,

1171
00:43:16,446 --> 00:43:16,806
yeah,

1172
00:43:16,806 --> 00:43:18,286
it's a historical fact.

1173
00:43:18,286 --> 00:43:20,066
We could have just called it lambda.

1174
00:43:21,546 --> 00:43:22,146
Okay,

1175
00:43:22,146 --> 00:43:23,726
so it's different than beta.

1176
00:43:23,946 --> 00:43:25,086
It's different than beta.

1177
00:43:25,086 --> 00:43:28,366
And historically,

1178
00:43:28,366 --> 00:43:31,486
lambda was set equal to beta times mu.

1179
00:43:31,926 --> 00:43:33,506
A little confusing there.

1180
00:43:33,666 --> 00:43:33,906
Yeah,

1181
00:43:33,906 --> 00:43:34,166
I know.

1182
00:43:34,306 --> 00:43:34,906
Great.

1183
00:43:35,106 --> 00:43:36,226
All right.

1184
00:43:37,346 --> 00:43:38,226
So we could have just called it lambda.

1185
00:43:40,326 --> 00:43:41,486
But that wouldn't be,

1186
00:43:41,486 --> 00:43:43,206
that would be ahistorical and it

1187
00:43:43,206 --> 00:43:44,926
would be different than the standard terminology.

1188
00:43:45,406 --> 00:43:47,426
So the standard terminology is

1189
00:43:47,426 --> 00:43:49,446
to replace lambda by beta mu.

1190
00:43:49,826 --> 00:43:52,106
But think of beta mu as itself a quantity.

1191
00:43:53,366 --> 00:43:53,846
Incidentally,

1192
00:43:53,846 --> 00:43:57,116
you calculate the average number of particles by differentiating

1193
00:43:57,116 --> 00:44:00,386
the logarithm of the partition function with respect to mu.

1194
00:44:01,686 --> 00:44:02,886
Differentiating with respect to mu,

1195
00:44:02,886 --> 00:44:03,066
well,

1196
00:44:03,066 --> 00:44:04,666
differentiating with respect to beta mu,

1197
00:44:04,666 --> 00:44:07,546
brings down an n and allows you

1198
00:44:07,546 --> 00:44:10,426
to calculate the average number of particles.

1199
00:44:10,546 --> 00:44:13,026
So you calculate the derivative of the logarithm

1200
00:44:13,026 --> 00:44:15,506
of the partition function with respect to beta mu.

1201
00:44:16,346 --> 00:44:19,766
And that gives you the mean number of particles,

1202
00:44:19,766 --> 00:44:21,866
which is very similar to

1203
00:44:21,866 --> 00:44:23,966
how we calculated the mean energy,

1204
00:44:24,646 --> 00:44:25,996
differentiate the log of the

1205
00:44:25,996 --> 00:44:27,346
partition function with respect to beta.

1206
00:44:27,566 --> 00:44:28,406
Similar idea.

1207
00:44:29,306 --> 00:44:29,866
Okay,

1208
00:44:29,866 --> 00:44:30,426
that's,

1209
00:44:30,426 --> 00:44:33,326
that is the basic setup for...

1210
00:44:33,326 --> 00:44:33,906
Yeah.

1211
00:44:34,446 --> 00:44:37,486
How does an experimentalist measure the chemical potential?

1212
00:44:37,866 --> 00:44:39,226
I know how they do temperature,

1213
00:44:39,226 --> 00:44:40,186
but how do you...

1214
00:44:40,186 --> 00:44:42,046
I'm not sure you do measure the chemical potential.

1215
00:44:42,246 --> 00:44:42,366
Yeah.

1216
00:44:44,246 --> 00:44:45,906
How do you measure the chemical potential?

1217
00:44:45,966 --> 00:44:47,766
I would say you measure the

1218
00:44:47,766 --> 00:44:49,566
density more likely than the chemical potential.

1219
00:44:54,945 --> 00:44:55,886
I don't know.

1220
00:44:55,926 --> 00:44:58,026
I never think about measuring the chemical potential.

1221
00:44:58,226 --> 00:44:59,796
I think of it as a

1222
00:44:59,796 --> 00:45:01,366
tunable parameter that changes the density,

1223
00:45:01,526 --> 00:45:03,306
and that the density is the thing that you...

1224
00:45:03,326 --> 00:45:05,866
Does that have anything to do with the work function?

1225
00:45:06,646 --> 00:45:07,126
Yeah,

1226
00:45:07,126 --> 00:45:08,886
it is the amount of energy that it

1227
00:45:08,886 --> 00:45:10,646
takes to remove a system from a box.

1228
00:45:10,866 --> 00:45:11,346
Yeah,

1229
00:45:11,346 --> 00:45:12,726
it is related to the work function.

1230
00:45:12,986 --> 00:45:14,586
So the work function is the energy?

1231
00:45:15,326 --> 00:45:15,806
Yeah,

1232
00:45:15,806 --> 00:45:17,526
how much energy it takes to

1233
00:45:17,526 --> 00:45:19,246
remove a particle from a box.

1234
00:45:19,986 --> 00:45:20,466
Yeah.

1235
00:45:22,066 --> 00:45:22,946
It's true.

1236
00:45:23,726 --> 00:45:24,206
Okay,

1237
00:45:24,206 --> 00:45:24,686
so...

1238
00:45:26,386 --> 00:45:26,866
Good.

1239
00:45:27,346 --> 00:45:30,106
But now I want to talk about something very exotic,

1240
00:45:30,106 --> 00:45:31,326
extremely interesting,

1241
00:45:31,506 --> 00:45:33,306
and took many years.

1242
00:45:33,326 --> 00:45:34,526
It took many years to really get right.

1243
00:45:35,366 --> 00:45:38,126
It has had an enormous influence

1244
00:45:38,126 --> 00:45:40,886
on statistical mechanics and quantum field theory.

1245
00:45:41,986 --> 00:45:46,126
I doubt that that's obvious to anybody in the room,

1246
00:45:46,146 --> 00:45:47,036
what all of this has

1247
00:45:47,036 --> 00:45:47,926
to do with quantum field theory,

1248
00:45:48,066 --> 00:45:51,546
but let's not worry about that.

1249
00:45:52,366 --> 00:45:55,216
It has to do with the behavior of

1250
00:45:55,216 --> 00:45:58,066
the system as you approach the critical point.

1251
00:45:58,426 --> 00:46:02,146
Let's say moving along h equals zero.

1252
00:46:02,146 --> 00:46:05,726
We don't even need h for this here.

1253
00:46:06,086 --> 00:46:09,846
We just move along from the high temperature side,

1254
00:46:10,126 --> 00:46:12,826
getting closer and closer to the critical point.

1255
00:46:12,946 --> 00:46:15,346
What is it that happens at the critical point?

1256
00:46:15,506 --> 00:46:17,046
And something very interesting

1257
00:46:17,046 --> 00:46:18,586
happens at the critical point.

1258
00:46:19,706 --> 00:46:21,846
The first idea that you need

1259
00:46:21,846 --> 00:46:23,986
in order to understand the critical point

1260
00:46:23,986 --> 00:46:25,666
is the idea of a correlation length.

1261
00:46:27,046 --> 00:46:27,886
We talked,

1262
00:46:27,886 --> 00:46:28,846
I think we talked,

1263
00:46:28,846 --> 00:46:31,266
did we talk at all about the correlation function?

1264
00:46:32,466 --> 00:46:33,066
No,

1265
00:46:33,066 --> 00:46:33,766
we didn't.

1266
00:46:33,806 --> 00:46:35,606
So I'll tell you what the correlation function is.

1267
00:46:35,666 --> 00:46:37,666
We don't need to talk about how you calculate it.

1268
00:46:38,486 --> 00:46:39,606
It's an average.

1269
00:46:40,306 --> 00:46:43,306
It's an average of the product

1270
00:46:43,306 --> 00:46:46,306
of spins at two different points.

1271
00:46:46,786 --> 00:46:49,666
Let's say sigma of A and sigma of B.

1272
00:46:50,286 --> 00:46:52,456
It's the average value of the

1273
00:46:52,456 --> 00:46:54,626
product of sigma A and sigma B.

1274
00:46:56,706 --> 00:46:59,126
It measures the degree of correlation

1275
00:46:59,766 --> 00:47:01,706
between the spin at point A

1276
00:47:02,146 --> 00:47:02,886
and the spin at point B.

1277
00:47:03,026 --> 00:47:05,126
These could be two points on the lattice.

1278
00:47:06,646 --> 00:47:08,086
They could be near each other.

1279
00:47:08,186 --> 00:47:09,446
They could be far from each other.

1280
00:47:09,806 --> 00:47:11,626
What happens if A is equal to B,

1281
00:47:11,626 --> 00:47:12,346
incidentally?

1282
00:47:14,646 --> 00:47:16,286
Sigma squared is just equal to one.

1283
00:47:16,706 --> 00:47:19,626
So the correlation function at the origin,

1284
00:47:19,626 --> 00:47:20,566
let's call it,

1285
00:47:22,786 --> 00:47:23,746
in other words,

1286
00:47:23,746 --> 00:47:25,286
when A and B are the same point,

1287
00:47:25,386 --> 00:47:26,586
that's always equal to one.

1288
00:47:27,265 --> 00:47:29,986
But now let's separate the points.

1289
00:47:30,366 --> 00:47:30,806
Okay?

1290
00:47:32,206 --> 00:47:32,826
All right.

1291
00:47:32,846 --> 00:47:34,766
So how do I calculate the correlation function

1292
00:47:34,766 --> 00:47:36,506
at these two different points?

1293
00:47:36,586 --> 00:47:37,106
And let's imagine,

1294
00:47:37,106 --> 00:47:39,406
let's go to extremely high temperatures.

1295
00:47:39,566 --> 00:47:41,606
Let's start at the high temperature end of things.

1296
00:47:42,166 --> 00:47:42,786
All right?

1297
00:47:42,806 --> 00:47:44,086
Not at the magnetized phase,

1298
00:47:44,086 --> 00:47:45,626
but at the high temperature end.

1299
00:47:46,266 --> 00:47:47,226
Infinite temperature,

1300
00:47:47,226 --> 00:47:48,686
enormously high temperature.

1301
00:47:48,886 --> 00:47:50,326
And what happens at very high temperature?

1302
00:47:50,766 --> 00:47:51,246
Eh,

1303
00:47:51,246 --> 00:47:52,786
jiggling around like mad.

1304
00:47:53,086 --> 00:47:54,706
And the temperature is so high

1305
00:47:54,706 --> 00:47:58,746
that the bonds are not very potent

1306
00:47:58,746 --> 00:48:00,846
at holding the spins aligned with each other.

1307
00:48:03,586 --> 00:48:06,726
So let's talk about the correlation,

1308
00:48:06,766 --> 00:48:07,726
or the average,

1309
00:48:07,726 --> 00:48:09,346
of the product of two spins

1310
00:48:10,026 --> 00:48:12,046
neighboring to each other at very,

1311
00:48:12,046 --> 00:48:14,026
very high temperature.

1312
00:48:14,246 --> 00:48:15,446
What would you expect that it would be?

1313
00:48:15,766 --> 00:48:16,226
Zero.

1314
00:48:17,606 --> 00:48:18,086
Zero,

1315
00:48:18,086 --> 00:48:20,406
because even if you freeze,

1316
00:48:20,626 --> 00:48:21,626
you can think of it this way.

1317
00:48:21,746 --> 00:48:23,326
You can think of calculating

1318
00:48:23,326 --> 00:48:24,906
it by freezing this spin up

1319
00:48:24,906 --> 00:48:27,386
and then calculating in the presence of this spin up,

1320
00:48:27,466 --> 00:48:29,126
calculating the average of this spin.

1321
00:48:30,246 --> 00:48:31,086
And then...

1322
00:48:32,046 --> 00:48:33,406
That's the way you can think about it.

1323
00:48:33,446 --> 00:48:35,216
It really represents the probability

1324
00:48:35,216 --> 00:48:36,986
that if this spin is up,

1325
00:48:37,126 --> 00:48:39,206
then this spin is also up,

1326
00:48:39,286 --> 00:48:40,486
or also down.

1327
00:48:40,626 --> 00:48:41,346
Some average,

1328
00:48:41,346 --> 00:48:43,566
given that this one is up,

1329
00:48:43,586 --> 00:48:46,306
what's the probability that this one is up or down?

1330
00:48:46,846 --> 00:48:47,866
And that represents,

1331
00:48:47,866 --> 00:48:49,186
that's the correlation function.

1332
00:48:49,366 --> 00:48:50,146
Or better yet,

1333
00:48:50,146 --> 00:48:51,966
given that this one is up,

1334
00:48:52,046 --> 00:48:53,486
what's the average of this one?

1335
00:48:53,926 --> 00:48:54,406
All right.

1336
00:48:55,225 --> 00:48:55,665
So,

1337
00:48:55,665 --> 00:48:56,706
what would you expect,

1338
00:48:56,706 --> 00:48:57,086
again,

1339
00:48:57,086 --> 00:48:58,026
at very high temperatures?

1340
00:48:58,906 --> 00:48:59,646
Just zero,

1341
00:48:59,646 --> 00:49:01,066
because they're fluctuating.

1342
00:49:01,086 --> 00:49:02,186
They're fluctuating completely independently,

1343
00:49:02,346 --> 00:49:04,386
because the temperature is so high

1344
00:49:04,386 --> 00:49:06,426
that the bond joining these is ineffective.

1345
00:49:07,286 --> 00:49:09,626
What happens as you start to lower the temperature?

1346
00:49:11,046 --> 00:49:12,886
As you start to lower the temperature,

1347
00:49:14,606 --> 00:49:17,106
if this spin is up,

1348
00:49:17,766 --> 00:49:20,706
it will bias this spin to also be up,

1349
00:49:20,886 --> 00:49:23,546
because the energy will be lowered if they're parallel.

1350
00:49:23,986 --> 00:49:25,506
If this spin is down,

1351
00:49:25,746 --> 00:49:28,086
it will also bias it.

1352
00:49:28,856 --> 00:49:30,186
So what starts to happen,

1353
00:49:31,086 --> 00:49:32,926
is that sigma times sigma

1354
00:49:32,926 --> 00:49:34,766
starts to not be zero anymore,

1355
00:49:35,986 --> 00:49:38,146
and in fact is usually positive.

1356
00:49:38,646 --> 00:49:41,646
It's positive because if this spin is up,

1357
00:49:41,706 --> 00:49:43,346
this one is more likely to be up,

1358
00:49:43,446 --> 00:49:45,266
so sigma times sigma is positive.

1359
00:49:45,836 --> 00:49:47,066
If this spin is down,

1360
00:49:47,246 --> 00:49:49,506
then this one is also more likely to be down,

1361
00:49:49,706 --> 00:49:50,526
and so again,

1362
00:49:50,526 --> 00:49:52,146
sigma times sigma is positive.

1363
00:49:52,836 --> 00:49:54,506
And so this correlation function

1364
00:49:55,706 --> 00:49:57,466
between neighboring points

1365
00:49:59,306 --> 00:50:01,186
at moderately high temperatures

1366
00:50:01,826 --> 00:50:03,366
will stop being zero

1367
00:50:03,366 --> 00:50:05,946
and be small but non-zero.

1368
00:50:06,126 --> 00:50:10,046
What about the correlation function

1369
00:50:10,046 --> 00:50:12,386
between second nearest neighbors?

1370
00:50:13,106 --> 00:50:13,666
Square?

1371
00:50:14,566 --> 00:50:16,226
Square is a negative one?

1372
00:50:16,426 --> 00:50:17,366
It'll be more or less,

1373
00:50:17,366 --> 00:50:17,726
that's right,

1374
00:50:17,806 --> 00:50:19,246
it'll be more or less the square

1375
00:50:20,166 --> 00:50:22,986
of the correlation between first nearest neighbors.

1376
00:50:23,246 --> 00:50:23,886
That's right.

1377
00:50:24,106 --> 00:50:25,926
That in fact is about what it is.

1378
00:50:25,926 --> 00:50:28,306
What about you go way,

1379
00:50:28,306 --> 00:50:29,326
way down the line here?

1380
00:50:30,506 --> 00:50:31,866
And there's nothing that's special

1381
00:50:31,866 --> 00:50:34,066
about moving along the horizontal axis here.

1382
00:50:34,226 --> 00:50:35,746
We move vertical axis,

1383
00:50:35,846 --> 00:50:37,166
or we can move at a 45 degree,

1384
00:50:37,326 --> 00:50:38,166
but what would you expect

1385
00:50:38,726 --> 00:50:39,986
as you move way down here?

1386
00:50:42,426 --> 00:50:42,946
Again,

1387
00:50:42,946 --> 00:50:44,746
you'll expect each time you move,

1388
00:50:44,846 --> 00:50:46,326
you'll lose some correlation.

1389
00:50:47,346 --> 00:50:48,326
And in fact,

1390
00:50:48,326 --> 00:50:50,026
you lose the same fraction

1391
00:50:50,026 --> 00:50:50,686
of correlation,

1392
00:50:50,686 --> 00:50:51,946
roughly speaking,

1393
00:50:52,106 --> 00:50:54,846
and that means that this is going to be

1394
00:50:54,846 --> 00:50:57,666
exponential in the distance between these points.

1395
00:50:58,066 --> 00:51:00,106
If each time you lost,

1396
00:51:00,106 --> 00:51:00,586
let's say,

1397
00:51:00,646 --> 00:51:02,086
half the correlation,

1398
00:51:02,406 --> 00:51:05,086
if the correlation between nearest neighbors

1399
00:51:05,086 --> 00:51:05,726
was a half,

1400
00:51:05,726 --> 00:51:07,486
and second nearest neighbors

1401
00:51:07,486 --> 00:51:08,046
was a quarter,

1402
00:51:08,046 --> 00:51:09,246
third nearest neighbors

1403
00:51:09,246 --> 00:51:09,906
was an eighth,

1404
00:51:09,906 --> 00:51:10,466
and so forth,

1405
00:51:10,626 --> 00:51:13,206
you might expect that this would behave

1406
00:51:13,846 --> 00:51:16,386
like e to the minus

1407
00:51:17,265 --> 00:51:19,126
some parameter m

1408
00:51:20,406 --> 00:51:22,646
times the distance between them.

1409
00:51:22,986 --> 00:51:24,826
Let's call it distance between them

1410
00:51:24,846 --> 00:51:25,166
d.

1411
00:51:25,926 --> 00:51:28,826
Distance means number of lattice sites

1412
00:51:28,826 --> 00:51:29,626
between them.

1413
00:51:30,366 --> 00:51:31,986
So when you're very,

1414
00:51:31,986 --> 00:51:32,846
very far away,

1415
00:51:34,665 --> 00:51:35,946
very far away,

1416
00:51:36,106 --> 00:51:38,266
the correlation is extremely weak,

1417
